  "body": "I am doing this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\ntry {\r\n    if (times) {\r\n      await HRE.run('verify', params)\r\n    } else {\r\n      console.error(\r\n        'Errors after all the retries, check the logs for more information.'\r\n      )\r\n    }\r\n  } catch (error) {\r\n    counter--\r\n    console.error(error.message)\r\n    await runTaskWithRetry(task, params, counter, msDelay, cleanup)\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis gets run when I want to verify contracts automatically. So far so good. \r\n\r\nThe problem is that `try` catch block fails and it goes into the catch block where the error states: `Contract source code already verified`.  What I want to do is that if the error is `already verified`, I want it to stop, otherwise recursively call (maybe there's some other mistakes which running it again would fix).\r\n\r\nThe only workaround I have is that in the catch block, I do the following:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nif(error.message != \"Contract source code already verified\"){\r\n   runTaskAgain();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo we have any better alternatives ? One can use `error instanceof NomicLabsHardhatPluginError` , but I don't think this would be correct, because `NomicLabsHardhatPluginError` could be thrown in some other cases as well.\r\n",
